\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"investor report\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:34:\"http://blog.mailchimp.com/?p=95561\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:300:\"MailChimp is weird in a lot of ways. One thing that makes us different from many other tech companies is that we dont have investors. Were privately owned, bootstrapped, and proud of it. We chart our own course, guided by our core values and the needs of our users. But one day a few months ...\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4:\"Lain\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2288:\"<figure class=\"img full-width\"><a href=\"http://mailchimp.com/about/investor-relations/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"//blog.mailchimp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/unspecified-1008x532.png\" alt=\"unspecified\" /></a></figure>\n<p>MailChimp is <a href=\"http://west-side-design-lab.tumblr.com\" target=\"_blank\">weird in a lot of ways</a>. One thing that makes us different from many other tech companies is that we dont have investors. Were privately owned, bootstrapped, and proud of it. We chart our own course, guided by our core values and the needs of our users.</p>\n<p>But one day a few months back it struck me that MailChimp actually does have investors: our 500 employees.</p>\n<p>We all work hard to make a great product and support our users. Were good at what we do, and our business is profitable. If we only cared about making money, wed just line our coffers and move on. But weve always thought ourselves as being part of a community, and that comes with great responsibility.</p>\n<p>Thats why, since 2013, weve investedmore than $3 million inorganizations in <a href=\"http://mailchimp.com/about/atlanta/\" target=\"_blank\">our hometown of Atlanta</a>.</p>\n<p>In particular, were committed to adding value to the many small and medium-sized nonprofits doing amazing work in the city. Organizations of this size are often unheralded underdogs, and we take pride in helping them succeed.</p>\n<p>But its not just about giving back or doing good. We expect something in return, but our ROI is pretty different too, I guess. What we want is an Atlanta thats better, weirder, and more human.</p>\n<p>This spring, we decided it was time to report back to our investors. We did this project for our employees, but were sharing it with the world to further elevate the individuals and organizations that inspire us. Have a look:</p>\n<p><a class=\"btn pop small size1of2 center\" href=\"http://mailchimp.com/about/investor-relations/\" target=\"_blank\">Read Our 2016 Investor Report</a></p>\n<p>Were proud of what weve accomplished so far, but theres always more work to do. Is there an organization or project you think we should know about? <a href=\"http://mailchimp.com/about/sponsorship/atlanta/\" target=\"_blank\">Send it our way</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:29:\"http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/\";a:1:{s:7:\"content\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:2:{s:3:\"url\";s:76:\"http://blog.mailchimp.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/unspecified-600x317.png\";s:6:\"medium\";s:5:\"image\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/Commen