INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (142,1,'2015-05-15 06:08:04','2015-05-15 06:08:04','This calculator is intended as a general guide only. The calculations are based on the accuracy of the information provided by you, and are based on various assumptions, including the following: \r\nThe number of points earned by spending at Fly Buys partners that makes up part of the ‘You Could Be Earning’ result is based on the assumption that you do all of your everyday spending with Fly Buys partners only (for example, all of your grocery shopping is done at New World supermarkets) and is based on current participating companies, qualifying goods and services and points collection rates. Fly Buys and its partners will from time to time determine which goods and services qualify for points collection, any minimum spend and the rate at which points may be collected for purchases of such goods and services. Points calculations are based on the following:\r\nGroceries. $25 = 1 Fly Buys point.\r\nFuel. 20 litres of fuel = 1 Fly Buys point. NOTE: this calculation will need to be updated as it only pertains to Z, if we are to include VTNZ, pitstop etc we will have to use all vehicle partners\r\nElectricity. Based on an average points collection rate of $50 = 1 Fly Buys point. NOTE only contact energy has been used in this calculation\r\nPharmacy. $25 = 1 Fly Buys point.\r\nHome Improvements. Based on an average points collection rate of $28=1 Fly Buys Point. Calculated by reference to those Fly Buys partners that fall within the home improvement category. \r\nTravel. Based on an average points collection rate of $26 = 1 Fly Buys point calculated by reference to those Fly Buys partners that fall within the travel category.\r\nThe number of points earned on BNZ products that makes up part of the ‘You Could Be Earning’ result is based on the assumption that: \r\nYou have a BNZ Classic Visa or MasterCard credit card, a BNZ Fly Buys home loan, and BNZ Fly Buys earning insurance; \r\nThe earn rate for purchases made with your Classic Visa or MasterCard credit card is 1 Fly Buys point per $50 spent; \r\nThe earn rate for your BNZ Standard/Fly Buys home loan is 9 Fly Buys points a month for home loan balances under $50,000, 34 Fly Buys points a month for home loan balances between $50,000 - $149,000 and 84 Fly Buys points a month for home loan balances over $150,000; and\r\nThe earn rate for your Fly Buys earning BNZ Insurance is 1 Fly Buys point for every $20 spent on insurance premium. \r\n\r\nFly Buys collection and redemption rates are subject to change without notice. For further details visit flybuys.co.nz. BNZ (and its related companies) do not guarantee the collection or redemption of Fly Buys points or that Fly Buys points will continue to be offered for products or services provided by them. LifeCare (link to:https://www.bnz.co.nz/assets/personal-banking/insurance/pdfs/2015-02-28-lifecare-general-terms.pdf), PremierCare (link to: https://www.bnz.co.nz/assets/about-us/terms-conditions/pdfs/premiercare-insurance-policy-document.pdf) and EasyCover (link to: https://www.bnz.co.nz/assets/about-us/terms-conditions/pdfs/1006-terms-and-conditions-EasyCover-insurance.pdf) insurance terms and conditions apply.)  EasyCover Insurance and LifeCare Insurance are underwritten by the insurer, BNZ Life Insurance Limited (“BNZ Life”), and is not an obligation of the distributor, Bank of New Zealand.  The obligations of BNZ Life are not guaranteed by its related companies, including National Australia Bank Limited and Bank of New Zealand, or any other parties.  BNZ arranges EasyCover and LifeCare as an agent for BNZ Life and receives a commission on any policies arranged through it.  Cover under PremierCare Insurance is subject to the terms, conditions and exclusions contained in the Policy Document and Schedule.  PremierCare Insurance is underwritten by the insurer, IAG New Zealand Limited (IAG NZ) and is not an obligation of the distributor, BNZ.  BNZ does not guarantee the obligations of IAG NZ.  BNZ arranges PremierCare Insurance as an agent for IAG NZ and receives a commission on any policies arranged through it. BNZ’s Qualifying Financial Entity Disclosure Statement may be obtained from any Bank of New Zealand store or Partners Centre, or viewed on Bank of New Zealand’s website bnz.co.nz.','Fly Buys Assumptions','','inherit','open','open','','98-revision-v1','','','2015-05-15 06:08:04','2015-05-15 06:08:04','',98,'http://flycalc.dev/98-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
